<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Time travellers capture four composers, lets say Mozart, Beethoven (first curing the deafness), Liszt and Shostakovich, imprison them in a mansion with four pianos and whatever language interpreters are needed, and demand they collaboratively write a symphony. </p> <p>And not just each writing a movement, they have to compose it together, with everyone having power of veto over everything, exactly like how some modern bands write. </p> <p>What happens next? Would the eventual output be as a great or even greater than the sum of the parts, or a confused mess after non-stop arguments?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/tau_decay"> /u/tau_decay </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wirax0/classical_music_written_in_collaboration/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/classicalmusic/comments/wirax0/classical_music_written_in_collaboration/">[comments]</a></span>